	&lt;span&gt;Privacy Policy&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/privacy/#privacy-policy" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="introduction"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Introduction&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/privacy/#introduction" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Personal data (usually referred to just as &amp;ldquo;data&amp;rdquo; below) is any information related to you which by itself or in cumulation with other pieces of information gives the opportunity to the person that collects and processes such information to identify you as a person. It can be your name, your identification number, your location data, or information related to your physical, physiological, genetic, mental, economic, cultural or social life. Such data will only be processed by us to the extent necessary and for the purpose of providing a functional and user-friendly website, including its contents, and the services offered there. The party responsible for this website (the &amp;ldquo;controller&amp;rdquo;) for purposes of data protection law can be found in the &lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/legal/"&gt;legal notice&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Getting Started</title><link>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/getting-started/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>vanruesc@outlook.de (Raoul van Rüschen)</author><guid>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/getting-started/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="getting-started"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Getting Started&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/getting-started/#getting-started" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="installation"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Installation&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/getting-started/#installation" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This library requires the peer dependency &lt;a href="https://github.com/mrdoob/three.js/"&gt;three&lt;/a&gt;. Check the &lt;a href="https://github.com/vanruesc/postprocessing/releases"&gt;release notes&lt;/a&gt; for supported versions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;npm install postprocessing
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="usage"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Usage&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/getting-started/#usage" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The following WebGL attributes should be used for an optimal workflow:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ts" data-lang="ts"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="kr"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;WebGLRenderer&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kr"&gt;from&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;three&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="kr"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;renderer&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;WebGLRenderer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;({&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;	&lt;span class="nx"&gt;powerPreference&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;high-performance&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;	&lt;span class="nx"&gt;antialias&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class="kt"&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;	&lt;span class="nx"&gt;stencil&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class="kt"&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;	&lt;span class="nx"&gt;depth&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class="kt"&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;});&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=""&gt;RenderPipelines&lt;/a&gt; are used to group passes. Common setups will only require one pipeline that contains a &lt;a href=""&gt;ClearPass&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=""&gt;GeometryPass&lt;/a&gt; and one or more &lt;a href=""&gt;EffectPass&lt;/a&gt; instances. The latter is used to render fullscreen &lt;a href=""&gt;Effects&lt;/a&gt;. Please refer to the &lt;a href="https://threejs.org/docs/#manual/en/introduction/Creating-a-scene"&gt;three.js manual&lt;/a&gt; for more information on how to setup the renderer, scene and camera.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Custom Passes</title><link>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/custom-passes/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>vanruesc@outlook.de (Raoul van Rüschen)</author><guid>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/custom-passes/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="custom-passes"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Custom Passes&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/custom-passes/#custom-passes" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="introduction"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Introduction&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/custom-passes/#introduction" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At a closer look, passes can be divided into four groups. The first group consists of passes that render normal scenes like the &lt;code&gt;GeometryPass&lt;/code&gt;. The second type doesn&amp;rsquo;t render anything but performs supporting operations like the &lt;code&gt;ClearPass&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;LambdaPass&lt;/code&gt;. Passes that render textures for further use make up the third group. One example would be the &lt;code&gt;LuminancePass&lt;/code&gt;. The fourth and most prominent group contains the fullscreen effect passes. If you want to make a pass that belongs to the last group, you should consider &lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/custom-effects/"&gt;creating an Effect&lt;/a&gt; instead.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Custom Effects</title><link>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/custom-effects/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>vanruesc@outlook.de (Raoul van Rüschen)</author><guid>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/custom-effects/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="custom-effects"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Custom Effects&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/custom-effects/#custom-effects" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="introduction"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Introduction&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/custom-effects/#introduction" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=""&gt;Effects&lt;/a&gt; are headless fullscreen passes. They can be combined and rendered using the &lt;a href=""&gt;EffectPass&lt;/a&gt;. Just like passes, effects may perform initialization tasks, react to render size changes and execute supporting render operations if needed but they don&amp;rsquo;t have access to a default output buffer and are not supposed to render to screen by themselves.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;details&gt;&lt;summary&gt;TL;DR&lt;/summary&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;shader.frag&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-glsl" data-lang="glsl"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;uniform&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;vec3&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;weights&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;vec4&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;mainImage&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;in&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;vec4&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;inputColor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;in&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;vec2&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;uv&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;in&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;GData&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;gData&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;	&lt;span class="k"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;vec4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;inputColor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;rgb&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;weights&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;inputColor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CustomEffect.js&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Plugins and Tools</title><link>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/plugins-tools/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>vanruesc@outlook.de (Raoul van Rüschen)</author><guid>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/plugins-tools/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="plugins-and-tools"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Plugins and Tools&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/plugins-tools/#plugins-and-tools" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The following third-party plugins and tools augment postprocessing and/or integrate it with other technologies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="react-postprocessing"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;react-postprocessing&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/plugins-tools/#react-postprocessing" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A postprocessing wrapper for &lt;a href="https://github.com/pmndrs/react-three-fiber"&gt;react-three-fiber&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/pmndrs/react-postprocessing"&gt;Repository&lt;/a&gt; · &lt;a href="https://github.com/pmndrs"&gt;@Poimandres&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="hyper-postprocessing"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;hyper-postprocessing&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/plugins-tools/#hyper-postprocessing" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;a href="https://github.com/vercel/hyper"&gt;Hyper&lt;/a&gt; plugin that makes it easy to attach fragment shaders to the terminal window.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/slammayjammay/hyper-postprocessing"&gt;Repository&lt;/a&gt; · &lt;a href="https://github.com/slammayjammay"&gt;@slammayjammay&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="three-material-editor"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;three-material-editor&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/plugins-tools/#three-material-editor" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A GLSL editor for Threejs materials. Automatically detect the WebGL programs and provide live edit for the shaders.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Migration Guide</title><link>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/migration-guide/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>vanruesc@outlook.de (Raoul van Rüschen)</author><guid>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/migration-guide/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="migration-guide"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Migration Guide&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/migration-guide/#migration-guide" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="v6--v7"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;v6 → v7&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/migration-guide/#v6--v7" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;RenderPass&lt;/code&gt; was replaced by &lt;code&gt;GeometryPass&lt;/code&gt;.
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A &lt;code&gt;ClearPass&lt;/code&gt; must now be used for clearing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;EffectComposer&lt;/code&gt; was replaced by &lt;code&gt;RenderPipeline&lt;/code&gt;.
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Most options have been moved to &lt;code&gt;GeometryPass&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The method &lt;code&gt;addPass&lt;/code&gt; was replaced by &lt;code&gt;add&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The method &lt;code&gt;render&lt;/code&gt; now expects a &lt;code&gt;timestamp&lt;/code&gt; parameter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The &lt;code&gt;EffectPass&lt;/code&gt; constructor no longer requires a &lt;code&gt;camera&lt;/code&gt; parameter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The &lt;code&gt;Pass.renderToScreen&lt;/code&gt; flag was removed.
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The last pass in the pipeline will automatically render to screen.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To force any pass to render to screen, set &lt;code&gt;pass.output.defaultBuffer&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;code&gt;null&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The same instances of &lt;code&gt;Pass&lt;/code&gt; can not be added to multiple &lt;code&gt;RenderPipelines&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The same instances of &lt;code&gt;Effect&lt;/code&gt; can not be added to multiple &lt;code&gt;EffectPasses&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>ASCII</title><link>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/special-effects/ascii/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>vanruesc@outlook.de (Raoul van Rüschen)</author><guid>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/special-effects/ascii/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="ascii"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;ASCII&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/special-effects/ascii/#ascii" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="external-resources"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;External Resources&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/special-effects/ascii/#external-resources" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;</description></item><item><title>Attribution</title><link>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/attribution/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>vanruesc@outlook.de (Raoul van Rüschen)</author><guid>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/attribution/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="attribution"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Attribution&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/attribution/#attribution" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="3d-models"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;3D Models&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/attribution/#3d-models" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h5 id="chocolate-bar"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Chocolate Bar&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/attribution/#chocolate-bar" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://sketchfab.com/3d-models/chocolate-bar-0d2dc2567a784fd28e9cb9a43c9f6505"&gt;Model&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href="https://sketchfab.com/youssefdarwish01"&gt;Fridge&lt;/a&gt;. Licensed under &lt;a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/"&gt;CC-BY 4.0&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5 id="crystal-stone"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Crystal Stone&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/attribution/#crystal-stone" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://sketchfab.com/3d-models/crystal-stone-rock-1ad829e2f464446fa4945562ab611255"&gt;Model&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href="https://sketchfab.com/geneugene"&gt;GenEugene&lt;/a&gt;. Licensed under &lt;a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/"&gt;CC-BY 4.0&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5 id="emissive-strength-test"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Emissive Strength Test&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/attribution/#emissive-strength-test" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/KhronosGroup/glTF-Sample-Assets/tree/eb4e2b0f96698a8f115ea7a70b60f8a442aca870/Models/EmissiveStrengthTest"&gt;Model&lt;/a&gt; and textures by Ed Mackey. Copyright 2022 Analytical Graphics, Inc. Licensed under &lt;a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/"&gt;CC-BY 4.0&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5 id="enchanted-crystal"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Enchanted Crystal&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/attribution/#enchanted-crystal" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
