&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://sketchfab.com/3d-models/enchanted-crystal-6b01945a041d4ed3b80e14274f0e68c9"&gt;Model&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href="https://sketchfab.com/TheTallOne"&gt;TheTallOne&lt;/a&gt;. Licensed under &lt;a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/"&gt;CC-BY 4.0&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5 id="plastic-garden-chair"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Plastic Garden Chair&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/attribution/#plastic-garden-chair" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://sketchfab.com/3d-models/monobloc-plastic-garden-chair-261d81ec28d845eba3bb7373768c60c5"&gt;Model&lt;/a&gt; and textures by &lt;a href="https://sketchfab.com/Pyromma-GS"&gt;Pyromma-GS&lt;/a&gt;. Licensed under &lt;a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/"&gt;CC-BY 4.0&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Bloom</title><link>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/light-shadow/bloom/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>vanruesc@outlook.de (Raoul van Rüschen)</author><guid>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/light-shadow/bloom/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="bloom"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Bloom&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/light-shadow/bloom/#bloom" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;BloomEffect&lt;/code&gt; uses a fast &lt;code&gt;MipmapBlurPass&lt;/code&gt; to blur bright scene highlights. By default, any colors that exceed the LDR range &lt;code&gt;[0.0, 1.0]&lt;/code&gt; will be affected by bloom. The luminance filter can be adjusting via the &lt;code&gt;luminanceThreshold&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;luminanceSmoothing&lt;/code&gt; settings. It can also be disabled entirely by setting &lt;code&gt;luminancePass.enabled&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;code&gt;false&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The mipmap blur algorithm downsamples the input buffer multiple times based on the number of &lt;code&gt;levels&lt;/code&gt;. At each level, the target buffer size is halved, creating a manual mipmap chain. After reaching the highest mipmap level, i.e. the smallest buffer size, the image is upsampled again using an additional support buffer at each level. The sampling patterns have been chosen carefully to create stable blurs with minimal aliasing, even at the screen&amp;rsquo;s edges. The following images roughly visualize the blurring process and the resulting bloom texture:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Blur</title><link>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/utility/blur/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>vanruesc@outlook.de (Raoul van Rüschen)</author><guid>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/utility/blur/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="blur"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Blur&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/utility/blur/#blur" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="external-resources"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;External Resources&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/utility/blur/#external-resources" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;</description></item><item><title>Color Depth</title><link>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/special-effects/color-depth/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>vanruesc@outlook.de (Raoul van Rüschen)</author><guid>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/special-effects/color-depth/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="color-depth"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Color Depth&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/special-effects/color-depth/#color-depth" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This effect simulates a hardware limitation to create a retro aesthetic. The real color depth remains unchanged.&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;blockquote class="alert alert-tip"&gt;
		&lt;div class="alert-heading"&gt;
			&lt;div class="alert-icon"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;span&gt;
				
					Tip
				
			&lt;/span&gt;
		&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;For best results, it&amp;rsquo;s recommended to apply this effect last, i. e. after tone mapping and antialiasing.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;h2 id="external-resources"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;External Resources&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/special-effects/color-depth/#external-resources" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.shadertoy.com/view/ldfXDH"&gt;Color depth reference shader&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>Depth Picking</title><link>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/utility/depth-picking/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>vanruesc@outlook.de (Raoul van Rüschen)</author><guid>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/utility/depth-picking/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="depth-picking"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Depth Picking&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/utility/depth-picking/#depth-picking" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A 2D point on screen can be converted into normalized device coordinates (NDC, -1 to 1 on each axis). The &lt;code&gt;DepthPickingPass&lt;/code&gt; uses the X and Y coordinates to read a single texel from the depth buffer back into a pixel array. The retrieved data is the raw depth at that location which completes the NDC. The obtained coordinates can be used to calculate the 3D world position based on the camera perspective/transformation matrices via unprojection.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>FXAA</title><link>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/anti-aliasing/fxaa/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>vanruesc@outlook.de (Raoul van Rüschen)</author><guid>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/anti-aliasing/fxaa/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="fast-approximate-anti-aliasing"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Fast Approximate Anti-Aliasing&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/anti-aliasing/fxaa/#fast-approximate-anti-aliasing" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FXAA is a lightweight, image-based anti-aliasing solution. It&amp;rsquo;s less stable in terms of shimmering compared to MSAA but oftentimes much faster. Its edge detection algorithm is based on luminance. The current implementation is based on FXAA version 3.11.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ts" data-lang="ts"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="kr"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;effect&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;FXAAEffect&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;({&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;minEdgeThreshold&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class="kt"&gt;0.0312&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;maxEdgeThreshold&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class="kt"&gt;0.125&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;subpixelQuality&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class="kt"&gt;0.75&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;samples&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class="kt"&gt;12&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;});&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;blockquote class="alert alert-tip"&gt;
		&lt;div class="alert-heading"&gt;
			&lt;div class="alert-icon"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;span&gt;
				
					Tip
				
			&lt;/span&gt;
		&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Anti-aliasing works best when applied after tone-mapping because it requires LDR input colors.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;h2 id="external-resources"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;External Resources&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/anti-aliasing/fxaa/#external-resources" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://developer.download.nvidia.com/assets/gamedev/files/sdk/11/FXAA_WhitePaper.pdf"&gt;FXAA white paper&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="http://blog.simonrodriguez.fr/articles/2016/07/implementing_fxaa.html"&gt;Implementing FXAA&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>Geometry Buffer</title><link>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/utility/gbuffer/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>vanruesc@outlook.de (Raoul van Rüschen)</author><guid>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/utility/gbuffer/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="geometry-buffer"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Geometry Buffer&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/utility/gbuffer/#geometry-buffer" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="geometrypass"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;GeometryPass&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/utility/gbuffer/#geometrypass" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;GeometryPass&lt;/code&gt; is responsible for rendering a scene and its output serves as the starting point in a render pipeline. This output is generally referred to as a &amp;ldquo;G-Buffer&amp;rdquo; and in its simplest form, it only consists of a single color texture attachment. With &lt;a href="https://registry.khronos.org/webgl/specs/latest/2.0/#3.7.11"&gt;MRT&lt;/a&gt; it&amp;rsquo;s possible to render to multiple buffers at once which enables more advanced effects. Without MRT, the entire scene would have to be rendered multiple times to obtain various types of geometry data.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Halftone</title><link>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/special-effects/halftone/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>vanruesc@outlook.de (Raoul van Rüschen)</author><guid>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/special-effects/halftone/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="halftone"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Halftone&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/special-effects/halftone/#halftone" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="external-resources"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;External Resources&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/special-effects/halftone/#external-resources" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;</description></item><item><title>Lens Distortion</title><link>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/utility/lens-distortion/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>vanruesc@outlook.de (Raoul van Rüschen)</author><guid>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/utility/lens-distortion/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="lens-distortion"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Lens Distortion&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/utility/lens-distortion/#lens-distortion" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="external-resources"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;External Resources&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/utility/lens-distortion/#external-resources" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;</description></item><item><title>LUT</title><link>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/color-grading/lut/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>vanruesc@outlook.de (Raoul van Rüschen)</author><guid>//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/color-grading/lut/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="color-grading-lut"&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Color Grading: LUT&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="//pmndrs.github.io/postprocessing/manual/demos/color-grading/lut/#color-grading-lut" data-pagefind-ignore&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;
